(267, 6, 1, '', '2014-12-20 05:21:36', 939, 3676, '35b97c909df12d36198e15a062a5028e9417bcf3', '{"id":6,"asset_id":"60","title":"CONTACT US_ARTICLE","alias":"contact-us-article","introtext":"<div class=\\"container_16\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\"grid_16\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\"wrapper\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\"grid_9 alpha_map\\">\\r\\n\\t<h2>how to find us<\\/h2>\\r\\n        <figure class=\\"img_inner\\">\\r\\n        <iframe src=\\"https:\\/\\/www.google.com\\/maps\\/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d922441.4639211831!2d31.794427!3d-25.4286678!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x1ee7d979f7ee32c7%3A0xc26a26336964d56c!2sMjejane+Private+Game+Reserve!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sza!4v1418642343510\\" width=\\"600\\" height=\\"450\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" style=\\"border:0\\"><\\/iframe>\\r\\n         <\\/figure>\\r\\n         <p>The Reserve is within easy access from all major centres \\u2013 approximately 4 hours\\u2019 drive from Gauteng, and a mere 45 minutes away from Kruger Mpumalanga International Airport with connecting flights from OR Tambo, Cape Town and Durban Airports.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Access to the reserve is gained via the N4, approximately 2,5km past the town of Hectorspruit, on the left side between Malelane and Komatipoort, en route to Maputo and Swaziland. Malelane town has a host of convenience shops, medical facilities and garages less than 10 minutes away, and three major golf courses are between 15 \\u2013 30 minutes drive from Mjejane.<\\/p>\\r\\n          <h2>Directions<\\/h2>\\r\\n               \\r\\n                   <p>BY AIR-Fly to KMIA, (the nearest airport).<\\/p>\\r\\n               <ul>\\r\\n                   <li>BY ROAD FROM THE NEARST CBD<\\/li>\\r\\n                   <li>By road from the nearest CBD - Nelspruit, take the N4<\\/li>\\r\\n                   <li>east to Hectorspruit. 2km''s further is Mjejane Game Reserve<\\/li>\\r\\n               <\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div class=\\"grid_7 omega\\">\\r\\n<h2>contact form<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\t{loadposition contact}\\r\\n\